n"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;KATHMANDU, Nepal — The Nepal Parliament building is a striking mix of old and new: a sprawling structure of steel and concrete capped off by a two-tier pagoda. But last week, its white walls were covered in soot and graffiti. "You picked the wrong fight," reads one message, signed: "Gen Z."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It's the fallout of the most dramatic upheaval the Himalayan country has experienced in years — where in less than 48 hours, protesters forced the overthrow of the government.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5545760-100" class="bucketwrap internallink mediapromo primary"&gt;             &lt;h4 class="internallink__slug"&gt;World&lt;/h4&gt;       &lt;h2 class="internallink__title"&gt;Nepal limps back to normalcy after massive protests toppled government&lt;/h2&gt;       &lt;article id="resnx-s1-9451849" class="bucketwrap resaudio" aria-label="audio-module"&gt;&lt;div class="audio-module"&gt;       &lt;h4 class="audio-module-title"&gt;Nepal limps back to normalcy after massive protests toppled government&lt;/h4&gt;    &lt;div class="audio-module-controls-wrap" data-audio='{"uid":"nx-s1-5539142:nx-s1-9451849","available":true,"duration":124,"title":"Nepal limps back to normalcy after massive protests toppled government","audioUrl":"https:\/\/ondemand.npr.org\/anon.npr-mp3\/npr\/me\/2025\/09\/20250915_me_nepal_limps_back_to_normalcy_after_massive_protests_toppled_government.mp3?t=progseg&amp;e=nx-s1-5521021&amp;p=3&amp;seg=13&amp;d=124&amp;size=1999561&amp;sc=siteplayer","storyUrl":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2025\/09\/15\/nx-s1-5539142\/nepal-limps-back-to-normalcy-after-massive-protests-toppled-government","slug":"World","program":"Morning Edition","affiliation":"","song":"","artist":"","album":"","track":0,"type":"segment","subtype":"other","skipSponsorship":false,"hasAdsWizz":false,"isStreamAudioType":false}' data-audio-metrics='[]'&gt;         &lt;div class="