%2F809c49c04a86a4c45bb40473593c%2Fgettyimages-2233912206.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3807x2538+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd3%2Fcd%2F809c49c04a86a4c45bb40473593c%2Fgettyimages-2233912206.jpg" class="img" alt="Fire rages through the Singha Durbar, the main administrative building for the Nepal government, in Kathmandu, on Sept. 9, a day after a police crackdown on demonstrations over social media prohibitions and corruption." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Fire rages through the Singha Durbar, the main administrative building for the Nepal government, in Kathmandu, on Sept. 9, a day after a police crackdown on demonstrations over social media prohibitions and corruption.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Prabin Ranabhat/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Prime Minister Khadga Prasad Oli resigned on Sept. 9 and has not been seen publicly since. The army imposed a curfew.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;By Sept. 12, the country had a new interim leader: Sushila Karki. The 73-year-old was &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/12/nx-s1-5539265/nepal-new-interim-prime-minister"&gt;Nepal's first female chief justice&lt;/a&gt; — and is now its first female prime minister. Her appointment by Nepal's president followed online polls on the chat portal Discord, where thousands supported her citing her judicial record of taking on the corrupt and the elite.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-89498" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5537;         --source-height: 3691;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5537x3691+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4f%2F7a%2Fe278d41446a39ba207aab7d96af5%2Fgettyimages-2234509457.jpg" class="img" alt="Prime minister of Nepal&amp;#039;s interim government, Sushila Karki (front right), arrives at the National Trauma Center hospital to visit victims injured in clashes with security personnel, in Kathmandu, on Sept. 13. Nepal&amp;#039;s capital on September 13, took a step back towards normality after deadly anti-corruption protests, as daily life returned with a curfew eased and an interim prime minister sworn into office. (Photo by Arun SANKAR / AFP) (Photo by ARUN SANKAR/AFP via Getty Images)" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Prime minister of Nepal's interim government, Sushila Karki (front right), arrives at the National Trauma Center hospital to visit victims injured in clashes with security personnel, in Kathmandu, on Sept. 13.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Arun Sankar/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5545760-101" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col"&gt;                     &lt;!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" --&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESNX-S1-5545760-101" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;"Our movement was motivated by two things," says Abhiyan Sapkota, a 27-year-old civil engineer who participated in the protests, "unemployment and government corruption."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For months, young Nepalis sought to highlight the stunning contrast between the country's masses and its wealthy elites, pulling together montages of social media images and videos uploaded by the children of prominent politicians. One image showed a young woman posing with a Prada bag worth $2,600, in a country where the average yearly income in Nepal is less than $1,500 a year.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;They zoomed in on Nepali elites vacationing in Europe, a contrast to the travels of most citizens — who work abroad in low-paying jobs as porters, soldiers and construction workers.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5545760-102" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col"&gt;                     &lt;!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" --&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESNX-S1-5545760-102" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The campaign, using variations of hashtags like #NepoKids, came amid mounting frustration with politicians who are widely seen as using public money to &lt;a href="https://kathmandupost.com/interviews/2025/09/14/gen-z-were-among-the-worst-affected-by-corruption" target="_blank"&gt;enrich themselves&lt;/a&gt;. "Over the last 10 years, all three individuals who have traded the prime minister's chair have had pretty serious corruption allegations against them," says &lt;a href="https://www.crisisgroup.org/who-we-are/our-people" target="_blank"&gt;Ashish Pradhan&lt;/a&gt;, an expert on Nepal at the International Crisis Group, a think tank.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Investigators never pursued the cases seriously, he says. "Instead, the anti-corruption watchdog was used to go after political opponents rather than to tackle systemic misuse of funds."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But on Sept. 4, the government abruptly suspended most social media. It was widely seen by anti-corruption activists as an attempt to quell their campaign exposing the poolside luxury lives of Nepal's elite. That led to thousands protesting in Kathmandu on Sept. 8.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-89502" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6912;         --source-height: 4608;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6912x4608+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb5%2Fac%2F65bcbd4b4c30b087869e70306064%2Fgettyimages-2233761207.jpg" class="img" alt="An aerial view shows demonstrators gathered outside Nepal&amp;#039;s Parliament during a protest in Kathmandu on Sept. 8." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 An aerial view shows demonstrators gathered outside Nepal's Parliament during a protest in Kathmandu on Sept. 8.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Prabin Ranabhat/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the days after violence, army personnel fanned out across the country. On major roads of Kathmandu, they set up checkpoints every few hundred yards and checked IDs. When curfew was relaxed for a few hours every day, youths &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/photo?fbid=1332775175088769&amp;set=a.255542386145392" target="_blank"&gt;cleaned&lt;/a&gt; the streets, visited hospitals to check upon the injured and held candlelight vigils for protesters who'd lost their lives. Outside a burnt-down police station in Kathmandu's Darbar Marg, someone scrawled an apology: "Sorry dada," Nepali for an elder brother.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-89503" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6230;         --source-height: 4153;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6230x4153+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F38%2Fd1%2F3436e82b43b28356f93291b71470%2Fgettyimages-2233764037.jpg" class="img" alt="A demonstrator shouts slogans during a protest outside the Parliament in Kathmandu on Sept. 8." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A demonstrator shouts slogans during a protest outside the Parliament in Kathmandu on Sept. 8.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Prabin Ranabhat/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The attacks on mainstream political parties also prompted introspection among some cadres.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Nepal has seen over a dozen coalition governments in the past two decades. But the top office has mostly rotated among the same set of leaders, most of them in their 70s. Now, some are &lt;a href="https://english.khojsamachar.com/gagan-thapa-apology-september-incidents-accountability-reform/" target="_blank"&gt;demanding&lt;/a&gt; a change in leadership. Pratima Gautam, member of the Nepali Congress party's central working committee, says the protesters had a message for the old guard: "Step back a little."&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;The uprising has come at a time of revolutionary fervor across South Asia.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5545760-103" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col"&gt;                     &lt;!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" --&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESNX-S1-5545760-103" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;"There are certainly some common threads between what we've seen in Nepal in the last week and what we seen in recent years in South Asian other countries, like Sri Lanka and Bangladesh, especially with cases of elite, long-standing regimes being deposed after crises that involved level of economic pressures that were being felt by citizens," says Pradhan, of the International Crisis Group.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The youth, he says, were spurred by rising costs of living and inflation, and reeling from the impact of climate change and COVID-19 lockdowns. Pradhan says the governments used force because they thought they could get away with it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;"The kind of international order and the checks and balances that were there in the glory days of the 1990s and parts of the 2000s have slowly eroded over time. The global picture now resembles a little bit more of a wild, wild west where might is right, and force and transactional diplomacy and mercantilism rule the day," he says.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-89508" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5094;         --source-height: 3396;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5094x3396+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0a%2F84%2F269e32b94f3d9e89d457e161dabd%2Fgettyimages-2234754221.jpg" class="img" alt="Nepal&amp;#039;s newly appointed interim prime minister, Sushila Karki, along with officials, observes a moment of silence for the people who died in recent protests, on Sept. 14." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Nepal's newly appointed interim prime minister, Sushila Karki, along with officials, observes a moment of silence for the people who died in recent protests, on Sept. 14.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Prabin Ranabhat/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Nepal is scheduled to hold elections early next year. Analysts say the challenge in front of the interim government is to maintain order and refrain from politics of retribution.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;There's optimism among the youth. When the interim leader took an oath a week ago, many defied curfew to sing and celebrate on the streets. The popular Instagram account Genz.Nepal summarized it in a pithy &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DOg5JdyEsx4/" target="_blank"&gt;post&lt;/a&gt;: "PM Sushila Karki… SLAYYY 💅🏼." The slang is a compliment.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But long-time Nepal watchers advise caution.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Political analyst Chandradev Bhatta says Nepal has a long history of regime-change through street protests. The national government has changed hands more than a dozen times in the last decade.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The instability has often been a result of tensions between democrats, monarchists, the Maoists and political parties. "If it was happening for the first time, I wouldn't have minded because we needed the change. But we've written seven constitutions in more than 70 years," Bhatta says.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5545760-104" class="bucketwrap statichtml"&gt;             &lt;blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/reel/DOt0rQNDoZG/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"&gt;&lt;div style="padding:16px;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/DOt0rQNDoZG/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;amp;utm_campaign=loading" style=" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;" target="_blank"&gt; &lt;div style=" display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center;"&gt; &lt;div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;"&gt; &lt;div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="padding: 19% 0;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="display:block; height:50px; margin:0 auto 12px; width:50px;"&gt;&lt;svg width="50px" height="50px" viewbox="0 0 60 60" version="1.1" xmlns="https://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="https://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"&gt;&lt;g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"&gt;&lt;g transform="translate(-511.000000, -20.000000)" fill="#000000"&gt;&lt;g&gt;&lt;path d="M556.869,30.41 C554.814,30.41 553.148,32.076 553.148,34.131 C553.148,36.186 554.814,37.852 556.869,37.